    <div class="wpd-comment-text">
    <p>I made these with native Juneberries (aka serviceberries, Amelanchier, sugarplum, etc.) and they were aMAZing!  The frozen berries (from a bumper 2009) harvest worked quite nicely!  Thank you for this recipe &#8212; and all the rest!</p>

</div>
