    <div class="wpd-space"></div>
    <div class="wpd-comment-link wpd-hidden">
    <span wpd-tooltip='Comment Link' wpd-tooltip-position='left'><i class='fas fa-link' aria-hidden='true' data-wpd-clipboard='https://www.theppk.com/2008/08/berry-week-day-1-marionberry-lavender-scones/#comment-24626'></i></span>
</div>
</div>
    
    <div class="wpd-comment-text">
    <p>[&#8230;] I won’t duplicate the recipe here for copyright reasons but it was a super simple mix of flour, salt, sugar, baking powder, olive oil, tomato sauce, and basil/rosemary. And scones are supposed to look all lumpy and asymmetrical, so I didn’t have to fuss over their appearance either. If you’d like to take a stab at another one of Isa’s scone recipes, I found this one online for Marionberry Lavender Scones. [&#8230;]</p>

</div>
