    <div class="wpd-space"></div>
    <div class="wpd-comment-link wpd-hidden">
    <span wpd-tooltip='Comment Link' wpd-tooltip-position='left'><i class='fas fa-link' aria-hidden='true' data-wpd-clipboard='https://www.theppk.com/2008/08/berry-week-day-1-marionberry-lavender-scones/#comment-24630'></i></span>
</div>
</div>
    
    <div class="wpd-comment-text">
    <p>I made these today, and they were so delicious.  I love lavender, and my BF who&#8217;s not crazy about &#8220;unusual&#8221; flavors didn&#8217;t seem to mind it at all.  </p>
<p>Allison &#8211; as long as you keep the earth balance butter very cold, it shouldn&#8217;t be a problem.  I&#8217;ve made a lot of scones like this &#8211; both vegan and non, and it&#8217;s a great soft biscuity texture, as long as you&#8217;re using shortening, or cold &#8220;butter.&#8221;</p>

</div>
